 <body bgcolor="white">
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Thousands of Americans piled into cars and buses with dogs, cats and duffel bags and left Clark Air Base today, 06/10/1991, after scientists warned that the eruption of a nearby volcano could turn catastrophic.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Lt. Col. Ron Rand announced the evacuation in a 5 a.m. 06/10/1991 broadcast over the U.S. military's Far East Network.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   An hour later, the first vehicles began rolling out of Clark for the U.S.-run Subic Bay naval base, where the 14,500 troops, dependents and civilian employees will be housed until the danger passes.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Another 1,500 troops remained at Clark to provide security.
  </a>
